00:01:27.570 --> 00:01:30.790 align:middle line:84%
when I released the
book and people asked--

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:34.666 align:middle line:84%
in October of 2011, that's
when the book was released,

00:01:34.666 --> 00:01:36.040 align:middle line:84%
one of the first
things I learned

00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:38.470 align:middle line:84%
is that truth means different
things to different people.

00:01:38.470 --> 00:01:41.410 align:middle line:84%
Truth is a bit of
a charged word.

00:01:41.410 --> 00:01:44.440 align:middle line:84%
Some people thought it was
presumptuous of me to write

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:45.910 align:middle line:90%
a book entitled Deep Truth.

00:01:45.910 --> 00:01:48.310 align:middle line:84%
You know, how can I
say this is the truth?

00:01:48.310 --> 00:01:50.339 align:middle line:84%
So I'd like to begin,
if we could, just

00:01:50.339 --> 00:01:51.880 align:middle line:84%
share a little bit
with our listeners

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:55.600 align:middle line:84%
about where that
title even came from.

00:01:55.600 --> 00:02:00.430 align:middle line:84%
This book was unique for me in
that I generally choose a title

00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:04.510 align:middle line:84%
and then write the book
directed toward the title.

00:02:04.510 --> 00:02:06.332 align:middle line:84%
This book was almost
complete before I

00:02:06.332 --> 00:02:07.540 align:middle line:90%
knew what the title would be.

00:02:07.540 --> 00:02:09.400 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know exactly
what the title

00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:11.230 align:middle line:90%
was going to be for this book.

00:02:11.230 --> 00:02:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And it was in a
bibliographical research piece,

00:02:17.170 --> 00:02:19.930 align:middle line:90%
bibliography of Niels Bohr--

00:02:19.930 --> 00:02:23.140 align:middle line:84%
20th century physicist,
colleague, and friend of Albert

00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:26.050 align:middle line:84%
Einstein-- that I discovered
the title of the book.

00:02:26.050 --> 00:02:28.000 align:middle line:84%
The two of them were
having a conversation,

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.950 align:middle line:84%
in the mid-20th century,
about the nature of truth.

00:02:32.950 --> 00:02:34.830 align:middle line:84%
And in this case,
their conversation,

00:02:34.830 --> 00:02:36.660 align:middle line:90%
it was scientific truth.

00:02:36.660 --> 00:02:38.180 align:middle line:90%
And this was 1940s.

00:02:38.180 --> 00:02:41.140 align:middle line:84%
It was like every week,
a new research paper

00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:43.030 align:middle line:84%
was being published
redefining what

00:02:43.030 --> 00:02:45.820 align:middle line:84%
we thought we knew about
the world of physics

00:02:45.820 --> 00:02:47.900 align:middle line:90%
and the laws of nature.

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.690 align:middle line:84%
And it was the comment
that Niels Bohr made

00:02:50.690 --> 00:02:54.794 align:middle line:84%
to Albert Einstein that it just
resonated with me so quickly,

00:02:54.794 --> 00:02:55.960 align:middle line:90%
and I'm just going to share.

00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:57.730 align:middle line:90%
It's a direct quote.

00:02:57.730 --> 00:03:03.180 align:middle line:84%
Niels Bohr said, "It is the
hallmark of any deep truth

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:06.490 align:middle line:84%
that its negation is
also a deep truth."

00:03:06.490 --> 00:03:07.570 align:middle line:90%
End of quote.

00:03:07.570 --> 00:03:09.240 align:middle line:90%
And I thought about that.

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:11.470 align:middle line:84%
And at first, I
thought, how profound.

00:03:11.470 --> 00:03:15.310 align:middle line:84%
So what he was saying is
when new discoveries overturn

00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:18.610 align:middle line:84%
the discoveries that we used
to think describe the deepest

00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:21.610 align:middle line:84%
truths of our existence, then
the new discoveries themselves

00:03:21.610 --> 00:03:23.200 align:middle line:90%
become the new deep truths.

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:25.330 align:middle line:84%
I said, that is precisely
where we find ourselves

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:26.130 align:middle line:90%
in the world today.

00:03:26.130 --> 00:03:28.350 align:middle line:84%
That's the title of my
new book, Deep Truth.

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.120 align:middle line:84%
>> And you go for every one
of these issues that are being

00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:32.710 align:middle line:90%
overturned as we speak.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:37.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there are so many
new discoveries that--

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:40.000 align:middle line:84%
peer-reviewed
scientific discoveries.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:41.800 align:middle line:84%
The book is not
based on speculation.

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:44.530 align:middle line:84%
It's not Gregg-ism
or my opinions

00:03:44.530 --> 00:03:47.050 align:middle line:90%
or new thoughts or new age.

00:03:47.050 --> 00:03:50.309 align:middle line:84%
It is based upon
peer-reviewed scientific fact.

00:03:50.309 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
And I did that
intentionally, Regina,

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:56.140 align:middle line:84%
because I wanted this book
to represent the deepest

00:03:56.140 --> 00:03:58.570 align:middle line:84%
truth of what we now understand
about our relationship

00:03:58.570 --> 00:04:00.820 align:middle line:90%
to ourselves and the world.

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:04.690 align:middle line:84%
And we have an audience
that I call the choir.

00:04:04.690 --> 00:04:07.230 align:middle line:84%
And I love the choir,
because the choir

00:04:07.230 --> 00:04:11.681 align:middle line:84%
has supported me, my work,
for almost 30 years now.

00:04:11.681 --> 00:04:13.930 align:middle line:84%
We're coming up on 30 years
that I've shared this work

00:04:13.930 --> 00:04:17.130 align:middle line:90%
in one form or another.

00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And have really worked
from a grassroots level

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:20.980 align:middle line:84%
to help us get the
work out there.

00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:23.650 align:middle line:84%
But what I know is this-- where
we find ourselves in the world

00:04:23.650 --> 00:04:28.130 align:middle line:84%
today, while the grassroots
comes from the bottom up,

00:04:28.130 --> 00:04:31.720 align:middle line:84%
we must work within the existing
power structures from the top

00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:36.040 align:middle line:84%
down if we are truly going to
bring about the kind of change,

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:38.620 align:middle line:84%
the degree, the
magnitude of change

00:04:38.620 --> 00:04:41.530 align:middle line:84%
that we're all talking about
in a very brief period of time.

00:04:41.530 --> 00:04:45.070 align:middle line:84%
We must work within
existing power structures

00:04:45.070 --> 00:04:46.870 align:middle line:84%
rather than trying
to do an end run

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:49.090 align:middle line:84%
or circumvent those
power structures.

00:04:49.090 --> 00:04:52.000 align:middle line:84%
And the only way to do
that in the Western world

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.250 align:middle line:84%
is to share the discoveries
in a language that

00:04:54.250 --> 00:04:56.010 align:middle line:90%
is respected and trusted.

00:04:56.010 --> 00:04:59.726 align:middle line:84%
And in the West, that language
is the language of science.

00:04:59.726 --> 00:05:01.600 align:middle line:84%
If I were to go into an
indigenous-- and I've

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:02.400 align:middle line:90%
done this.

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:04.790 align:middle line:84%
When I go into the monasteries
of Tibet and to Egypt,

00:05:04.790 --> 00:05:07.360 align:middle line:84%
for example, and I talk
to the monks or the nuns

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:09.100 align:middle line:84%
about new scientific
discoveries,

00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.990 align:middle line:84%
the first thing
they do is giggle,

00:05:10.990 --> 00:05:12.700 align:middle line:84%
because it's
unimportant to them.

00:05:12.700 --> 00:05:14.050 align:middle line:90%
Who needs the discoveries?

00:05:14.050 --> 00:05:16.490 align:middle line:90%
They live the principles.

00:05:16.490 --> 00:05:19.930 align:middle line:84%
But in the Western world,
because our choices

00:05:19.930 --> 00:05:23.110 align:middle line:90%
are impacting the whole world--

00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:24.790 align:middle line:84%
very, very few
places in the world

00:05:24.790 --> 00:05:28.330 align:middle line:84%
that the choices that we're
making now of how we deal,

00:05:28.330 --> 00:05:31.450 align:middle line:84%
adapt to climate change or
confront climate change, how

00:05:31.450 --> 00:05:35.560 align:middle line:84%
we deal with new diseases,
how we deal with the inability

00:05:35.560 --> 00:05:37.930 align:middle line:84%
to grow the food to support
the global populations,

00:05:37.930 --> 00:05:42.340 align:middle line:84%
disappearing of fresh water,
the disparity between wealth

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:44.620 align:middle line:84%
and poverty, the
growing disparity,

00:05:44.620 --> 00:05:48.470 align:middle line:84%
the growing disparity between
illiteracy and education--

00:05:48.470 --> 00:05:52.780 align:middle line:84%
these are just the tip of the
iceberg of the kinds of crises

00:05:52.780 --> 00:05:54.370 align:middle line:84%
the best minds of
our time tell us

00:05:54.370 --> 00:05:55.620 align:middle line:90%
that we are facing right now.

00:05:55.620 --> 00:05:57.660 align:middle line:84%
They say it's not
our imagination,

00:05:57.660 --> 00:05:59.840 align:middle line:84%
that this generation,
this time in history,

00:05:59.840 --> 00:06:02.290 align:middle line:84%
we are, in fact,
facing the greatest

00:06:02.290 --> 00:06:04.960 align:middle line:84%
number and the greatest
magnitude of crises

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:08.860 align:middle line:84%
ever to face a single
generation in 5,000 years

00:06:08.860 --> 00:06:10.030 align:middle line:90%
of recorded human history.

00:06:10.030 --> 00:06:12.070 align:middle line:84%
And they're telling
us that we've

00:06:12.070 --> 00:06:16.990 align:middle line:84%
got, in some cases, less than
two years, less than 24 months,

00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:20.080 align:middle line:84%
to change the way we think to
address some of the crises.

00:06:20.080 --> 00:06:24.010 align:middle line:84%
And even less than that when
it comes to the big war that's

00:06:24.010 --> 00:06:25.600 align:middle line:90%
looming over the Middle East.

00:06:25.600 --> 00:06:27.210 align:middle line:90%
I think we all sense that.

00:06:27.210 --> 00:06:31.540 align:middle line:84%
Or when it comes to the collapse
of a global economic system.

00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:34.900 align:middle line:84%
We have less than two years
to figure those things out.

00:06:34.900 --> 00:06:37.960 align:middle line:84%
The same people that
tell us of the crises

00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:41.090 align:middle line:84%
are telling us that they exist
because of a way of thinking,

00:06:41.090 --> 00:06:43.810 align:middle line:84%
that the crises are
the out-picturing

00:06:43.810 --> 00:06:46.376 align:middle line:84%
of a way of thinking
and a way of living

00:06:46.376 --> 00:06:47.500 align:middle line:90%
that's led to those crises.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:50.440 align:middle line:84%
So if we try to solve them
through the same thinking that

00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:53.170 align:middle line:84%
created them, we know
where that's going to lead.

00:06:53.170 --> 00:06:56.230 align:middle line:84%
So the book describes
new discoveries.

00:06:56.230 --> 00:06:59.530 align:middle line:84%
The good news is that
there are a series

00:06:59.530 --> 00:07:02.050 align:middle line:84%
of new scientific
discoveries that

00:07:02.050 --> 00:07:06.010 align:middle line:84%
overturn the deepest truths
that we held of our past.

00:07:06.010 --> 00:07:08.230 align:middle line:84%
The new discoveries now
become the new deep truths.

00:07:08.230 --> 00:07:09.760 align:middle line:90%
That's the good news.

00:07:09.760 --> 00:07:14.600 align:middle line:84%
The flip side is that there is
a reluctance and, in some cases,

00:07:14.600 --> 00:07:18.880 align:middle line:84%
an outright resistance
to share this information

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:20.740 align:middle line:90%
in the mainstream.

00:07:20.740 --> 00:07:23.800 align:middle line:84%
What I mean by that
is mainstream media,

00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:27.070 align:middle line:84%
mainstream documentaries,
mainstream television,

00:07:27.070 --> 00:07:30.640 align:middle line:84%
mainstream classrooms,
mainstream textbooks.

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:33.719 align:middle line:84%
A reluctance, in some cases
an outright resistance--

00:07:33.719 --> 00:07:36.010 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to be very
clear with our listeners here.

00:07:36.010 --> 00:07:39.310 align:middle line:84%
When I talk about the classroom,
it's not the teacher's fault.

00:07:39.310 --> 00:07:41.080 align:middle line:84%
In the United
States of America--

00:07:41.080 --> 00:07:43.600 align:middle line:84%
because I know people view
this beyond our borders.

00:07:43.600 --> 00:07:45.970 align:middle line:84%
But in the United
States of America,

00:07:45.970 --> 00:07:50.380 align:middle line:84%
every teacher is bound by a
covenant within the specific

00:07:50.380 --> 00:07:54.580 align:middle line:84%
state where they teach that
determines what can and cannot

00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:56.920 align:middle line:84%
be shared publicly in the
classroom if it's a publicly

00:07:56.920 --> 00:07:58.550 align:middle line:90%
funded classroom.

00:07:58.550 --> 00:08:00.460 align:middle line:84%
And every state is
a little different,

00:08:00.460 --> 00:08:03.880 align:middle line:84%
and some of the states,
there are common themes,

00:08:03.880 --> 00:08:07.210 align:middle line:84%
such as the teaching of what can
and cannot be shared regarding

00:08:07.210 --> 00:08:10.840 align:middle line:84%
human evolution is one of
the places where this--

00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:13.570 align:middle line:84%
or climate change,
this comes up a lot.

00:08:13.570 --> 00:08:17.470 align:middle line:84%
So the good news is that new
discoveries have shown us

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:19.660 align:middle line:84%
where the thinking
of the past can

00:08:19.660 --> 00:08:24.700 align:middle line:84%
be revised to reflect a deeper
reality, a deeper truth.

00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:28.090 align:middle line:84%
The flip side is that
mainstream's not getting that.

00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:31.660 align:middle line:84%
So I chose five of
those principles

00:08:31.660 --> 00:08:34.720 align:middle line:84%
that I call false assumptions
of science, five that I think

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:37.419 align:middle line:84%
have had perhaps
the greatest impact

00:08:37.419 --> 00:08:38.860 align:middle line:84%
on our lives and
our world today,

00:08:38.860 --> 00:08:42.600 align:middle line:84%
and I described those five
in the new book Deep Truth,

00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:46.210 align:middle line:84%
subtitle Igniting the Memory of
our Origin, History, Destiny,

00:08:46.210 --> 00:08:47.830 align:middle line:90%
and Fate.

00:08:47.830 --> 00:08:50.060 align:middle line:84%
>> And in this book, I mean,
you're talking about all

00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:52.780 align:middle line:84%
the most essential
