00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:03.530 align:middle line:84%
But you're also talking
about the species,

00:09:03.530 --> 00:09:08.220 align:middle line:84%
to reflecting on ourselves
in a different way now.

00:09:08.220 --> 00:09:09.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:13.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Darwinian theory of
evolution isn't working anymore.

00:09:13.270 --> 00:09:14.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Darwin's part of it.

00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:20.500 align:middle line:84%
The key for me of the many new
discoveries that have been made

00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:23.980 align:middle line:84%
and are made-- peer-reviewed
scientific discoveries that

00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:27.100 align:middle line:84%
completely changed the way
we've been led to think about

00:09:27.100 --> 00:09:29.110 align:middle line:84%
our relationship to our
bodies, our relationship

00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:31.360 align:middle line:84%
to the physical world, our
relationship to the Earth,

00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:34.150 align:middle line:84%
our relationship to
history, to the past,

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:37.720 align:middle line:84%
civilizations the past,
of the many discoveries--

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:40.780 align:middle line:84%
I chose five that I think are,
perhaps, having the greatest

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:44.920 align:middle line:84%
impact on the crises
that we have today.

00:09:44.920 --> 00:09:48.940 align:middle line:84%
And the thinking that can make
the greatest amount of change

00:09:48.940 --> 00:09:52.670 align:middle line:84%
in the least amount of time
regarding those crises.

00:09:52.670 --> 00:09:57.040 align:middle line:84%
So what it really boiled down
to, Regina, was simply this--

00:09:57.040 --> 00:09:59.740 align:middle line:84%
the best minds of our
time are telling us,

00:09:59.740 --> 00:10:01.840 align:middle line:84%
in no uncertain
terms, that we're

00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:04.780 align:middle line:84%
facing the greatest crises
of our very existence,

