I was trained as a scientist.

00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:17.712 align:middle line:90%
I think science is good.

00:19:17.712 --> 00:19:19.170 align:middle line:84%
I believe in the
scientific method.

00:19:19.170 --> 00:19:21.720 align:middle line:84%
I think our lives are certainly
better because of science,

00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.580 align:middle line:90%
in some respects.

00:19:23.580 --> 00:19:25.710 align:middle line:84%
Science does not
have all the answers.

00:19:25.710 --> 00:19:27.900 align:middle line:90%
Science is a young language.

00:19:27.900 --> 00:19:31.380 align:middle line:84%
It's a young way of looking
and thinking of our world.

00:19:31.380 --> 00:19:33.760 align:middle line:90%
It's only about 300 years old.

00:19:33.760 --> 00:19:36.810 align:middle line:84%
So I think Darwin was probably
a pretty good scientist.

00:19:36.810 --> 00:19:39.550 align:middle line:84%
In my opinion, here's
where he made his mistake.

00:19:39.550 --> 00:19:41.430 align:middle line:90%
Here's where Darwin went wrong.

00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.550 align:middle line:84%
Charles Darwin took
observations that he

00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:48.600 align:middle line:84%
made for some forms of life
in some parts of the world,

00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:51.370 align:middle line:84%
and he tried to apply them
to all life everywhere,

00:19:51.370 --> 00:19:53.260 align:middle line:90%
including human life.

00:19:53.260 --> 00:19:55.571 align:middle line:84%
And the data simply
doesn't support it.

00:19:55.571 --> 00:19:56.820 align:middle line:90%
So here's what I mean by that.

00:19:56.820 --> 00:20:01.410 align:middle line:84%
He would go into nature,
and he would see examples

00:20:01.410 --> 00:20:05.120 align:middle line:90%
of birds, two siblings--

00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:05.920 align:middle line:90%
same species.

00:20:05.920 --> 00:20:08.760 align:middle line:84%
They were siblings in
a nest, young birds.

00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:12.270 align:middle line:84%
Another bird of another species
would come into that nest,

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:16.050 align:middle line:84%
and the two that were there
originally would immediately

00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:19.320 align:middle line:84%
eject the bird from the nest
because it was different.

00:20:19.320 --> 00:20:23.160 align:middle line:84%
Or he saw colonies
of larger ants

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:26.850 align:middle line:84%
capturing smaller
colonies of ants

00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:28.110 align:middle line:90%
and making slaves out of them.

00:20:28.110 --> 00:20:29.160 align:middle line:90%
They didn't kill them.

00:20:29.160 --> 00:20:32.410 align:middle line:84%
They enslaved them to
do their work for them.

00:20:32.410 --> 00:20:35.070 align:middle line:84%
Darwin, in his way
of thinking, he

00:20:35.070 --> 00:20:36.960 align:middle line:84%
believed that when
he saw these things,

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:39.040 align:middle line:90%
little examples in nature.

00:20:39.040 --> 00:20:41.130 align:middle line:84%
He believed they were
small expressions

00:20:41.130 --> 00:20:44.090 align:middle line:84%
of a general law that
applies to everybody,

00:20:44.090 --> 00:20:45.630 align:middle line:90%
and we've heard this law before.

00:20:45.630 --> 00:20:49.770 align:middle line:84%
The law is multiply,
vary, let the strongest

00:20:49.770 --> 00:20:51.880 align:middle line:90%
live and the weakest die.

00:20:51.880 --> 00:20:54.690 align:middle line:84%
Let the strongest live
and the weakest die.

00:20:54.690 --> 00:20:57.370 align:middle line:84%
It's a very, very
dangerous way of thinking.

00:20:57.370 --> 00:20:59.110 align:middle line:90%
1859.

00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:02.890 align:middle line:84%
Because it was the
first scientific attempt

00:21:02.890 --> 00:21:05.950 align:middle line:84%
to describe our
relationship to the world,

00:21:05.950 --> 00:21:09.370 align:middle line:84%
his idea was embraced quickly
without a lot of investigation.

00:21:09.370 --> 00:21:11.380 align:middle line:84%
People just accepted
it as science,

00:21:11.380 --> 00:21:13.150 align:middle line:90%
so it was embraced quickly.

00:21:13.150 --> 00:21:17.700 align:middle line:84%
It became very deeply entrenched
in the emerging modern world.

00:21:17.700 --> 00:21:21.970 align:middle line:84%
And Regina, it's so much
a part of our lives today.

00:21:21.970 --> 00:21:24.340 align:middle line:84%
Every one of us, our
listeners, no matter

00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:27.400 align:middle line:84%
how conscious we believe
we are and how much

00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:30.670 align:middle line:84%
work we've done with ourselves,
subconsciously, this idea

00:21:30.670 --> 00:21:33.790 align:middle line:84%
is so ingrained
into the way that we

00:21:33.790 --> 00:21:37.240 align:middle line:84%
have been taught to live,
to think, the systems

00:21:37.240 --> 00:21:40.420 align:middle line:84%
that we've grown to
rely upon for our lives.

00:21:40.420 --> 00:21:43.380 align:middle line:84%
We've been taught that
it's a dog-eat-dog world,

00:21:43.380 --> 00:21:45.490 align:middle line:84%
that if we don't go
out there and fight,

00:21:45.490 --> 00:21:48.730 align:middle line:84%
