00:28:51.730 --> 00:28:53.260 align:middle line:90%
of thinking.

00:28:53.260 --> 00:28:57.550 align:middle line:84%
So here we are, right now, the
early years, the 21st century.

00:28:57.550 --> 00:29:00.610 align:middle line:84%
We are living the last year
of a rare and mysterious cycle

00:29:00.610 --> 00:29:06.130 align:middle line:84%
of time, a 5,125-year-long cycle
our ancestors called the Great

00:29:06.130 --> 00:29:07.900 align:middle line:90%
World Age.

00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:10.690 align:middle line:84%
They knew that the cycle was
coming, because it always does,

00:29:10.690 --> 00:29:17.560 align:middle line:84%
every 5,125 years, because
Earth's location in space

00:29:17.560 --> 00:29:20.230 align:middle line:90%
changes on a rhythmic basis.

00:29:20.230 --> 00:29:22.420 align:middle line:84%
That location, they
knew, would change

00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:25.780 align:middle line:84%
the way we live on Earth,
the way we live in our lives.

00:29:25.780 --> 00:29:28.690 align:middle line:84%
Earth's location as
it changes in space,

00:29:28.690 --> 00:29:31.240 align:middle line:90%
it changes the climate.

00:29:31.240 --> 00:29:32.710 align:middle line:90%
It changes the weather patterns.

00:29:32.710 --> 00:29:35.960 align:middle line:84%
It changes the way we're
able to grow our food,

00:29:35.960 --> 00:29:39.355 align:middle line:84%
the way we're able
to share resources.

00:29:39.355 --> 00:29:42.130 align:middle line:90%
It happens every 5,000 years.

00:29:42.130 --> 00:29:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And that change is what triggers
within us the ways of dealing

00:29:48.610 --> 00:29:51.940 align:middle line:84%
with problems, and it tells us
what works and what doesn't.

00:29:51.940 --> 00:29:54.940 align:middle line:84%
Our thinking of competition
and survival of the strongest,

00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:58.180 align:middle line:84%
if we try to address
this great change

00:29:58.180 --> 00:30:00.220 align:middle line:84%
through that way
of thinking, we're

00:30:00.220 --> 00:30:01.870 align:middle line:90%
already seeing where it leads.

00:30:01.870 --> 00:30:04.600 align:middle line:84%
Because it's leading to the
collapse of ways of life

00:30:04.600 --> 00:30:07.150 align:middle line:84%
that we have grown to
cherish in the past.

00:30:07.150 --> 00:30:11.590 align:middle line:84%
So it's an opportunity to
change that way of thinking.

00:30:11.590 --> 00:30:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And the new discoveries give
us a good reason to do so,

00:30:14.500 --> 00:30:16.580 align:middle line:84%
except they're not being
shared on a public--

00:30:16.580 --> 00:30:17.380 align:middle line:90%
>> No, they're not.

00:30:17.380 --> 00:30:18.300 align:middle line:90%
And here, at the same time--

00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:18.820 align:middle line:90%
>> --mainstream level.

00:30:18.820 --> 00:30:20.230 align:middle line:84%
>> --as all of
this is happening,

00:30:20.230 --> 00:30:25.270 align:middle line:84%
the squeeze is happening, and
the fittest here economically--

00:30:25.270 --> 00:30:27.530 align:middle line:84%
who aren't doing so well,
by the way, right now.

00:30:27.530 --> 00:30:29.777 align:middle line:84%
A handful of people have
made out all right on this.

00:30:29.777 --> 00:30:30.610 align:middle line:90%
But what's happened?

00:30:30.610 --> 00:30:33.160 align:middle line:84%
It's come at the expense of
virtually everything else.

00:30:33.160 --> 00:30:37.549 align:middle line:84%
What has happened to the poet,
to the artist, to the musician?

00:30:37.549 --> 00:30:39.340 align:middle line:84%
When you start looking
into the things that

00:30:39.340 --> 00:30:43.720 align:middle line:84%
make life an expression, that's
the first thing squeezed out

00:30:43.720 --> 00:30:47.590 align:middle line:84%
in favor of the most
functional types of positions

00:30:47.590 --> 00:30:50.890 align:middle line:90%
that only serve that machine.

00:30:50.890 --> 00:30:52.330 align:middle line:90%
And so we're at that point now.

00:30:52.330 --> 00:30:53.130 align:middle line:90%
>> We are.

00:30:53.130 --> 00:30:56.380 align:middle line:84%
>> And again, I think this
ties back into what you're--

00:30:56.380 --> 00:30:58.760 align:middle line:84%
you know Michael Cremo, as
well, Forbidden Archeology.

00:30:58.760 --> 00:30:59.760 align:middle line:90%
>> I know him very well.

00:30:59.760 --> 00:31:00.940 align:middle line:90%
