00:31:06.604 --> 00:31:08.020 align:middle line:84%
He's a brilliant
man, amazing man.

00:31:08.020 --> 00:31:09.830 align:middle line:84%
>> He's a brilliant
man, and one of the--

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:10.630 align:middle line:90%
>> And a brother.

00:31:10.630 --> 00:31:11.230 align:middle line:90%
>> And a brother.

00:31:11.230 --> 00:31:12.634 align:middle line:90%
He's another of your brothers.

00:31:12.634 --> 00:31:14.050 align:middle line:84%
And I've interviewed
your brother.

00:31:14.050 --> 00:31:17.260 align:middle line:84%
I think he's a he's
an incredible man.

00:31:17.260 --> 00:31:18.676 align:middle line:84%
And what he's
saying about this--

00:31:18.676 --> 00:31:20.800 align:middle line:84%
because it's going to take
you back into the theory

00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:25.150 align:middle line:84%
of evolution and back into what
we are, what has inspired us--

00:31:25.150 --> 00:31:27.970 align:middle line:84%
is that the theory of
evolution has become

00:31:27.970 --> 00:31:31.600 align:middle line:84%
institutionalized because it
actually serves another larger

00:31:31.600 --> 00:31:33.370 align:middle line:90%
kind of agenda.

00:31:33.370 --> 00:31:34.180 align:middle line:90%
>> It's habit.

00:31:34.180 --> 00:31:34.720 align:middle line:90%
>> It's habit.

00:31:34.720 --> 00:31:37.000 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a lot of money
invested in supporting that

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:37.520 align:middle line:90%
story.

00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:38.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you bet.

00:31:38.320 --> 00:31:41.260 align:middle line:84%
And it also keeps people limited
in our perceptions of self

00:31:41.260 --> 00:31:42.860 align:middle line:90%
and our own capabilities.

00:31:42.860 --> 00:31:44.110 align:middle line:90%
And that's not helping things.

00:31:44.110 --> 00:31:47.740 align:middle line:84%
>> It can, but this is where
I think we have an opportunity

00:31:47.740 --> 00:31:52.084 align:middle line:84%
to really rethink the way
we think about ourselves

00:31:52.084 --> 00:31:53.500 align:middle line:84%
and our relationship
to the Earth.

00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:56.432 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people out there
saying we made a lot of mistakes

00:31:56.432 --> 00:31:57.640 align:middle line:90%
and really screwed things up.

00:31:57.640 --> 00:31:59.120 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe that at all.

00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:00.130 align:middle line:90%
What I believe is this.

00:32:00.130 --> 00:32:02.470 align:middle line:84%
I think we're in a
huge learning curve.

00:32:02.470 --> 00:32:06.040 align:middle line:84%
And I think the choices
that we made as individuals

00:32:06.040 --> 00:32:08.560 align:middle line:84%
and as a civilization
in the past

00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:11.210 align:middle line:84%
have been based on what
we knew at the time.

00:32:11.210 --> 00:32:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And we made choices
based on what we knew.

00:32:13.570 --> 00:32:16.300 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's all
we can ask of ourselves.

00:32:16.300 --> 00:32:20.080 align:middle line:84%
Now we have the opportunity
to make new choices,

00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:23.140 align:middle line:84%
and new information is
out there to inform us.

00:32:23.140 --> 00:32:26.060 align:middle line:84%
And where the problem comes in
is when that information is not

00:32:26.060 --> 00:32:26.860 align:middle line:90%
shared.

00:32:26.860 --> 00:32:29.244 align:middle line:90%
Evolution is one example.

00:32:29.244 --> 00:32:30.160 align:middle line:90%
So now, let's go back.

00:32:30.160 --> 00:32:33.720 align:middle line:84%
I've just shared-- now, this
is one deep truth, number five,

00:32:33.720 --> 00:32:37.257 align:middle line:84%
that nature is based upon
survival of the strongest.

00:32:37.257 --> 00:32:38.840 align:middle line:84%
We now know that's
a false assumption.

00:32:38.840 --> 00:32:42.430 align:middle line:84%
It's based on mutual
aid and cooperation.

00:32:42.430 --> 00:32:46.620 align:middle line:84%
While competition can happen in
response to certain situations,

00:32:46.620 --> 00:32:48.890 align:middle line:90%
it's not the rule of nature.

00:32:48.890 --> 00:32:51.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm to pop up
to deep truth number

00:32:51.340 --> 00:32:53.050 align:middle line:90%
two about civilization itself.

00:32:53.050 --> 00:32:54.758 align:middle line:84%
This is where it gets
really interesting,

00:32:54.758 --> 00:32:57.410 align:middle line:90%
and context so important.

00:32:57.410 --> 00:33:00.060 align:middle line:84%
We're taught that 5,000 years
is the age of civilization.

00:33:00.060 --> 00:33:01.610 align:middle line:90%
It's a one-time deal.

00:33:01.610 --> 00:33:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And I remember studying
my history books.

00:33:04.390 --> 00:33:07.180 align:middle line:84%
And here's like 5,000 years
ago was Ancient Sumeria.

00:33:07.180 --> 00:33:09.989 align:middle line:84%
Egypt is more recent
and Rome and Greece.

00:33:09.989 --> 00:33:11.530 align:middle line:84%
All things I thought
were so ancient,

00:33:11.530 --> 00:33:13.750 align:middle line:90%
they're actually more recent.

00:33:13.750 --> 00:33:16.487 align:middle line:84%
And I remember asking
our professors,

00:33:16.487 --> 00:33:17.570 align:middle line:90%
what happened before that?

00:33:17.570 --> 00:33:19.390 align:middle line:84%
And they said it's
like nothing was going.

00:33:19.390 --> 00:33:21.977 align:middle line:84%
On Nobody here,
nothing was happening.

00:33:21.977 --> 00:33:24.310 align:middle line:84%
The archaeological evidence
doesn't support that at all.

00:33:24.310 --> 00:33:26.674 align:middle line:84%
Peer-reviewed archaeological
evidence-- now,

00:33:26.674 --> 00:33:28.840 align:middle line:84%
I've had the opportunity
to personally document some

00:33:28.840 --> 00:33:30.580 align:middle line:90%
of these sites myself--

00:33:30.580 --> 00:33:34.120 align:middle line:84%
are now pushing the age
of advanced civilization

00:33:34.120 --> 00:33:38.020 align:middle line:84%
back into the last ice age,
the end of the last ice age.

00:33:38.020 --> 00:33:41.350 align:middle line:84%
Now, as a former geologist,
what I can say to our listeners

00:33:41.350 --> 00:33:44.380 align:middle line:84%
is the ice age ended
about 12,000 years ago.

00:33:44.380 --> 00:33:46.630 align:middle line:84%
After that, there
was 4,000 years

00:33:46.630 --> 00:33:47.860 align:middle line:90%
of what's called a bad storm.

00:33:47.860 --> 00:33:48.670 align:middle line:90%
Really bad storm.

00:33:48.670 --> 00:33:51.160 align:middle line:90%
It lasted 4,000 years.

00:33:51.160 --> 00:33:52.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's at the
end of the ice age

00:33:52.900 --> 00:33:56.200 align:middle line:84%
and during the bad storm
when the temperatures rose.

00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:57.230 align:middle line:90%
There was a lot of rain.

00:33:57.230 --> 00:33:58.030 align:middle line:90%
The ice melted.

00:33:58.030 --> 00:33:58.900 align:middle line:90%
The sea levels rose.

00:33:58.900 --> 00:34:04.210 align:middle line:84%
That's when this last cycle
of civilization formed.

00:34:04.210 --> 00:34:07.330 align:middle line:84%
So now, we have places--
the oldest site right now

00:34:07.330 --> 00:34:08.889 align:middle line:90%
is called Gobekli Tepe.

00:34:08.889 --> 00:34:11.110 align:middle line:90%
It's in Turkey.

00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:13.282 align:middle line:84%
Archaeologists have
not even excavated

00:34:13.282 --> 00:34:15.865 align:middle line:84%
to the bottom of the site, and
they're already dating this now

00:34:15.865 --> 00:34:17.920 align:middle line:90%
at 13,500 years old.

00:34:17.920 --> 00:34:20.199 align:middle line:84%
That's over twice as
old as what we've been

00:34:20.199 --> 00:34:21.969 align:middle line:90%
led to believe in the past.

00:34:21.969 --> 00:34:25.389 align:middle line:84%
Other sites, Catal Hoyuk,
another site in Turkey,

00:34:25.389 --> 00:34:27.370 align:middle line:90%
8,000 to 9,000 years old.

00:34:27.370 --> 00:34:32.679 align:middle line:84%
Off the coast of India,
under 120 feet of water,

00:34:32.679 --> 00:34:37.639 align:middle line:84%
there is a site that is five
miles long, two miles wide.

00:34:37.639 --> 00:34:41.562 align:middle line:90%
It is under 120 feet of water.

00:34:41.562 --> 00:34:44.020 align:middle line:84%
I have to say, it's a sign that
one of two things happened.

00:34:44.020 --> 00:34:45.603 align:middle line:84%
Either the site was
built under water,

00:34:45.603 --> 00:34:47.949 align:middle line:84%
which could happen
but isn't likely,

00:34:47.949 --> 00:34:50.590 align:middle line:84%
or it was built near
the water, and when

00:34:50.590 --> 00:34:55.449 align:middle line:84%
the climate changed and the sea
levels rose, it was submerged.

00:34:55.449 --> 00:34:57.460 align:middle line:84%
>> So these are pre-ice
age in some cases?

00:34:57.460 --> 00:34:59.620 align:middle line:84%
>> These are all right at
the edge of the ice age.

00:34:59.620 --> 00:35:02.047 align:middle line:90%
The ice age is 12,000 years.

00:35:02.047 --> 00:35:03.880 align:middle line:84%
So some of these are
right back at-- they're

00:35:03.880 --> 00:35:06.490 align:middle line:84%
dating now 13,500,
right around in there.

00:35:06.490 --> 00:35:09.010 align:middle line:84%
But they haven't gotten to
the bottom of these yet.

00:35:09.010 --> 00:35:09.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:35:09.850 --> 00:35:12.820 align:middle line:84%
>> I personally
documented northern Peru.

00:35:12.820 --> 00:35:15.010 align:middle line:90%
There's a site called Caral.

00:35:15.010 --> 00:35:16.114 align:middle line:90%
Caral, Peru.

00:35:16.114 --> 00:35:17.530 align:middle line:84%
We don't know who
built this site.

00:35:17.530 --> 00:35:19.810 align:middle line:84%
It's a 150-acre
site, five pyramids,

00:35:19.810 --> 00:35:23.260 align:middle line:90%
two huge circular plazas.

00:35:23.260 --> 00:35:24.980 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where
they came from.

00:35:24.980 --> 00:35:26.230 align:middle line:90%
We don't know where they went.

00:35:26.230 --> 00:35:27.550 align:middle line:90%
But here's the thing.

00:35:27.550 --> 00:35:31.330 align:middle line:84%
The day I was there is when the
laboratories-- the university

00:35:31.330 --> 00:35:34.930 align:middle line:84%
called my translator with
the dating for the site.

00:35:34.930 --> 00:35:37.760 align:middle line:84%
The day I was there is when
the dates were revealed.

00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:40.580 align:middle line:84%
We're taught that civilization
began 5,000 years ago.

00:35:40.580 --> 00:35:41.830 align:middle line:90%
That's when Caral ended.

00:35:41.830 --> 00:35:44.110 align:middle line:84%
It ended when we're
told that civilization

00:35:44.110 --> 00:35:48.680 align:middle line:84%
began and dates back at least
2,000 years older than that.

00:35:48.680 --> 00:35:49.480 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me.

00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:50.390 align:middle line:90%
And there are other sites.

00:35:50.390 --> 00:35:52.720 align:middle line:84%
But the reason I'm sharing
this, if it were one site,

00:35:52.720 --> 00:35:54.400 align:middle line:90%
it could be an anomaly.

00:35:54.400 --> 00:35:56.680 align:middle line:84%
Now what's happening
is the anomalies

00:35:56.680 --> 00:36:00.270 align:middle line:84%
are telling a new story, and
the story is simply this.

00:36:00.270 --> 00:36:02.090 align:middle line:84%
The 5,000 years that
we've been taught

00:36:02.090 --> 00:36:04.710 align:middle line:84%
is the history of the
whole world forever,

00:36:04.710 --> 00:36:06.710 align:middle line:84%
it's not the history of
the whole world forever.

00:36:06.710 --> 00:36:10.850 align:middle line:84%
It's the history of the most
recent 5,000-year cycle based

00:36:10.850 --> 00:36:13.670 align:middle line:90%
on Earth's alignment in space.

00:36:13.670 --> 00:36:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And before that, there was
another 5,000-year cycle that

00:36:17.390 --> 00:36:19.910 align:middle line:84%
almost universally indigenous
traditions refer to.

00:36:19.910 --> 00:36:22.754 align:middle line:84%
They call it the Golden
Age or the Age of Peace.

00:36:22.754 --> 00:36:24.170 align:middle line:84%
And there were
cycles before that.

00:36:24.170 --> 00:36:25.296 align:middle line:90%
>> Before that, yes.

00:36:25.296 --> 00:36:26.795 align:middle line:84%
>> I cannot say
that scientifically.

00:36:26.795 --> 00:36:28.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Scientifically, it
cannot be verified,

00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:29.240 align:middle line:90%
but it's been in the lore--

00:36:29.240 --> 00:36:30.040 align:middle line:90%
>> It has.

00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>> --of every indigenous culture
that they've gone on back

00:36:33.230 --> 00:36:34.070 align:middle line:90%
throughout.

00:36:34.070 --> 00:36:38.420 align:middle line:84%
>> At least four cycles,
each cycle 5,000 years long.

00:36:38.420 --> 00:36:40.010 align:middle line:84%
At least four of
those in the past.

00:36:40.010 --> 00:36:41.810 align:middle line:84%
We can scientifically
validate two of them.

00:36:41.810 --> 00:36:45.470 align:middle line:84%
As a geologist, we can
validate the characteristics

00:36:45.470 --> 00:36:46.599 align:middle line:90%
of the four cycles.

00:36:46.599 --> 00:36:48.140 align:middle line:84%
But here's why I'm
even sharing this.

00:36:48.140 --> 00:36:50.000 align:middle line:84%
This is where it gets
really interesting.

00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:54.110 align:middle line:84%
There is a through line
that links all of these

00:36:54.110 --> 00:36:57.990 align:middle line:84%
pre-5,000-year cycles
together, civilizations,

00:36:57.990 --> 00:37:00.110 align:middle line:90%
and it simply is this.

00:37:00.110 --> 00:37:02.390 align:middle line:84%
In every one of
those sites, there's

00:37:02.390 --> 00:37:04.540 align:middle line:90%
no evidence of any weapons.

00:37:04.540 --> 00:37:07.880 align:middle line:84%
There's no evidence
of large-scale war.

00:37:07.880 --> 00:37:12.920 align:middle line:10%
There are no walls surrounding
the homes or the cities

00:37:12.920 --> 00:37:14.710 align:middle line:10%
to protect them
as we find today.

00:37:14.710 --> 00:37:16.340 align:middle line:84%
There are no moats
surrounding them.

00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:18.290 align:middle line:84%
There are no mass
burials that you

00:37:18.290 --> 00:37:21.140 align:middle line:84%
would expect after large-scale
war, no mutilated bodies.

00:37:21.140 --> 00:37:25.014 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's true of the
Gulf of Khambhat in India.

00:37:25.014 --> 00:37:26.430 align:middle line:84%
That's true of the
sites in Egypt.

00:37:26.430 --> 00:37:28.680 align:middle line:84%
That's true of
the sites in Peru.

00:37:28.680 --> 00:37:30.680 align:middle line:84%
It's true of the
sites in Turkey,

00:37:30.680 --> 00:37:33.170 align:middle line:84%
as well as those through
the Ukraine and Europe

00:37:33.170 --> 00:37:34.249 align:middle line:90%
that we're finding.

00:37:34.249 --> 00:37:35.540 align:middle line:90%
One of two things is happening.

00:37:35.540 --> 00:37:39.590 align:middle line:84%
Either those things exist
and they haven't been found

00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:41.990 align:middle line:90%
or they're non-existent.

00:37:41.990 --> 00:37:45.520 align:middle line:84%
To me, if the
weapons were there,

00:37:45.520 --> 00:37:47.270 align:middle line:84%
if there were evidence
of large-scale war,

00:37:47.270 --> 00:37:48.860 align:middle line:84%
I think, in at
least one site, we

00:37:48.860 --> 00:37:51.580 align:middle line:84%
would have found some
shred of evidence.

00:37:51.580 --> 00:37:54.380 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that we have
not is leading historians

00:37:54.380 --> 00:37:58.940 align:middle line:84%
and archaeologists to rewrite
portions of the history books

00:37:58.940 --> 00:38:00.129 align:middle line:90%
in peer-reviewed articles.

00:38:00.129 --> 00:38:01.670 align:middle line:84%
It's not being shared
in our schools,

00:38:01.670 --> 00:38:03.320 align:middle line:90%
but what they're saying is this.

00:38:03.320 --> 00:38:05.060 align:middle line:84%
What they're saying
is it appears now

00:38:05.060 --> 00:38:08.720 align:middle line:84%
that war is not human nature,
that it's not our nature

00:38:08.720 --> 00:38:11.570 align:middle line:84%
to fight one another
and destroy one another.

00:38:11.570 --> 00:38:15.080 align:middle line:84%
That war appears to be a
habit, a very bad habit, that

00:38:15.080 --> 00:38:18.380 align:middle line:90%
began about 5,000 years ago.

00:38:18.380 --> 00:38:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Interestingly, during the time
that we say civilization began.

00:38:22.620 --> 00:38:24.890 align:middle line:84%
But before that time,
there's no evidence

00:38:24.890 --> 00:38:26.150 align:middle line:90%
of any large-scale war.

00:38:26.150 --> 00:38:29.180 align:middle line:84%
And it suggests that
if war is a habit that

00:38:29.180 --> 00:38:31.040 align:middle line:84%
was learned 5,000
years ago, then

00:38:31.040 --> 00:38:33.200 align:middle line:84%
it's a habit that
we can unlearn.

00:38:33.200 --> 00:38:38.330 align:middle line:84%
The crises of today may force
us to come to that realization,

00:38:38.330 --> 00:38:41.630 align:middle line:84%
because the purpose of
war is now obsolete.

00:38:41.630 --> 00:38:46.360 align:middle line:84%
The idea that there is someone
that is clearly a winner,

00:38:46.360 --> 00:38:49.741 align:middle line:84%
there's a loser, you know
when the war is over--

00:38:49.741 --> 00:38:51.990 align:middle line:84%
the wars we're looking at
today are not about borders.

00:38:51.990 --> 00:38:53.014 align:middle line:90%
They're about ideas.

00:38:53.014 --> 00:38:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think almost every
mother has always known war is

00:38:55.430 --> 00:38:57.455 align:middle line:90%
obsolete.

00:38:57.455 --> 00:38:59.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, and it certainly is now.

00:38:59.180 --> 00:39:02.940 align:middle line:84%
So now, we put this into the
context of these deep truths,

00:39:02.940 --> 00:39:06.890 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not surprised that
we find no evidence of war,

00:39:06.890 --> 00:39:10.340 align:middle line:84%
because it is not in our
deepest nature, survival

00:39:10.340 --> 00:39:11.270 align:middle line:90%
of the strongest.

00:39:11.270 --> 00:39:14.750 align:middle line:84%
We are, essentially,
a cooperative species.

00:39:14.750 --> 00:39:15.770 align:middle line:90%
We can compete.

00:39:15.770 --> 00:39:18.200 align:middle line:84%
We can kill each other
and blow one another up,

00:39:18.200 --> 00:39:20.390 align:middle line:84%
we know that, under
certain conditions.

00:39:20.390 --> 00:39:23.480 align:middle line:84%
Where this gets really
even more interesting

00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:27.140 align:middle line:84%
is the researchers have found
three conditions, Regina,

00:39:27.140 --> 00:39:32.600 align:middle line:84%
they say, under
which we will betray

00:39:32.600 --> 00:39:37.310 align:middle line:84%
our truest nature of
cooperation and survival

00:39:37.310 --> 00:39:39.710 align:middle line:90%
or cooperation and mutual aid.

00:39:39.710 --> 00:39:40.550 align:middle line:90%
Three conditions.

00:39:40.550 --> 00:39:44.930 align:middle line:84%
If one or some combination of
these three conditions exist.

00:39:44.930 --> 00:39:47.780 align:middle line:84%
Number one, when we feel
personally threatened,

00:39:47.780 --> 00:39:49.430 align:middle line:90%
we can become violent.

00:39:49.430 --> 00:39:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Number two, when we feel that
our families are threatened.

00:39:52.880 --> 00:39:56.247 align:middle line:84%
Number three, when we feel that
our way of life is threatened.

00:39:56.247 --> 00:39:57.830 align:middle line:84%
You look at the hot
spots in the world

00:39:57.830 --> 00:40:00.830 align:middle line:84%
today, especially in the
Middle East and Africa,

00:40:00.830 --> 00:40:03.979 align:middle line:84%
and not only one of
those but, in many cases,

00:40:03.979 --> 00:40:05.270 align:middle line:90%
all three of those are present.

00:40:05.270 --> 00:40:08.310 align:middle line:84%
People feel their lives,
their way of life,

00:40:08.310 --> 00:40:10.817 align:middle line:84%
their families are being
threatened right now.

00:40:10.817 --> 00:40:12.900 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not saying it's
right, wrong, good, or bad.

00:40:12.900 --> 00:40:14.441 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying at some
point, ultimately,

00:40:14.441 --> 00:40:16.579 align:middle line:84%
if you really want to get
to the bottom of this,

00:40:16.579 --> 00:40:18.120 align:middle line:84%
we're going to have
to address those.

00:40:18.120 --> 00:40:22.640 align:middle line:84%
But I think it's
useful to know that--

00:40:22.640 --> 00:40:26.844 align:middle line:84%
to me, it feels different to
know that war and conflict is

00:40:26.844 --> 00:40:27.760 align:middle line:90%
not our truest nature.

00:40:27.760 --> 00:40:31.370 align:middle line:84%
There is a history
book that is used

00:40:31.370 --> 00:40:33.597 align:middle line:84%
as a textbook in many
mainstream classrooms today,

00:40:33.597 --> 00:40:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and the first page
of the history book

00:40:35.180 --> 00:40:39.110 align:middle line:84%
actually says, quote,
"War is like commerce.

00:40:39.110 --> 00:40:41.830 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
all humans do."

00:40:41.830 --> 00:40:43.455 align:middle line:84%
So they lead us to
believe that it's

00:40:43.455 --> 00:40:44.790 align:middle line:90%
as natural as night and day.

00:40:44.790 --> 00:40:47.800 align:middle line:84%
So we have a generation
of young people--

00:40:47.800 --> 00:40:50.462 align:middle line:84%
war looks very sexy on the
commercials on the television.

00:40:50.462 --> 00:40:52.670 align:middle line:84%
>> They're doing some
feature-length films on it that

00:40:52.670 --> 00:40:54.253 align:middle line:84%
are being released,
I think, in March.

00:40:54.253 --> 00:40:57.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, I look them and I
think if I didn't know how it

00:40:57.650 --> 00:41:00.710 align:middle line:84%
was being used, that would
be cool a very cool thing.

00:41:00.710 --> 00:41:02.234 align:middle line:90%
High tech, very cool.

00:41:02.234 --> 00:41:03.650 align:middle line:84%
Young people are
being conditioned

00:41:03.650 --> 00:41:06.470 align:middle line:84%
to believe you've got
to go out and fight

00:41:06.470 --> 00:41:08.090 align:middle line:90%
for your piece of the pie.

00:41:08.090 --> 00:41:09.680 align:middle line:84%
And you start it
from the early age,

00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:10.820 align:middle line:84%
and you start it
in the classroom

00:41:10.820 --> 00:41:11.410 align:middle line:90%
with the kid next to you.

00:41:11.410 --> 00:41:13.180 align:middle line:84%
>> You start it on video
games with little kids.

00:41:13.180 --> 00:41:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>> They do.

00:41:13.980 --> 00:41:14.930 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:41:14.930 --> 00:41:17.120 align:middle line:90%
So now, again, context.

00:41:17.120 --> 00:41:21.670 align:middle line:84%
Here we are, the last year
of a 5,125-year cycle.

00:41:21.670 --> 00:41:24.250 align:middle line:84%
Earth's position in
space has changed,

00:41:24.250 --> 00:41:26.420 align:middle line:84%
changes the
conditions that we've

00:41:26.420 --> 00:41:27.800 align:middle line:90%
learned to live with on Earth.

00:41:27.800 --> 00:41:29.330 align:middle line:90%
And it's forcing us now--

00:41:29.330 --> 00:41:31.030 align:middle line:90%
it's forcing our hand.

00:41:31.030 --> 00:41:33.350 align:middle line:84%
It's forcing us
to change the way

00:41:33.350 --> 00:41:35.942 align:middle line:84%
that we have lived
in the past, the way

00:41:35.942 --> 00:41:38.150 align:middle line:84%
that we solve our problems,
the way we grow our food,

00:41:38.150 --> 00:41:41.690 align:middle line:84%
the way we share our resources,
the way we share medicines.

00:41:41.690 --> 00:41:44.550 align:middle line:84%
The question is this, and
we're answering it right now,

00:41:44.550 --> 00:41:51.880 align:middle line:84%
will we choose cooperation
or competition?

00:41:51.880 --> 00:41:54.140 align:middle line:84%
I think it's a much
more basic question.

00:41:54.140 --> 00:41:55.850 align:middle line:84%
I think we're asking
will we choose love,

00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:57.624 align:middle line:90%
or will we choose fear?

00:41:57.624 --> 00:41:59.540 align:middle line:84%
I don't know the answer
to that, because we're

00:41:59.540 --> 00:42:00.810 align:middle line:90%
making the choice right now.

00:42:00.810 --> 00:42:02.490 align:middle line:84%
But I'm encouraged
by what I'm seeing.

00:42:02.490 --> 00:42:05.040 align:middle line:84%
I think we're going to get
very close to a big war

00:42:05.040 --> 00:42:05.840 align:middle line:90%
in the Middle East.

00:42:05.840 --> 00:42:07.842 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's
going to happen.

00:42:07.842 --> 00:42:09.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm encouraged by what
I see behind the scenes.

00:42:09.800 --> 00:42:14.120 align:middle line:84%
I think the crises are
forcing us to work together

00:42:14.120 --> 00:42:16.340 align:middle line:84%
in ways that we've
never had to, personally

00:42:16.340 --> 00:42:19.120 align:middle line:84%
and on a global level,
because we need to now.

00:42:19.120 --> 00:42:19.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:42:19.940 --> 00:42:23.990 align:middle line:84%
>> I think what will happen
is when the crises subside,

00:42:23.990 --> 00:42:27.024 align:middle line:84%
because we now already
are working together,

00:42:27.024 --> 00:42:28.190 align:middle line:90%
we'll keep working together.

00:42:28.190 --> 00:42:30.273 align:middle line:84%
Because we'll find that
we're better people and we

00:42:30.273 --> 00:42:31.590 align:middle line:90%
have a better world.

00:42:31.590 --> 00:42:34.640 align:middle line:84%
And in that way, some of the
most beautiful prophecies

00:42:34.640 --> 00:42:37.430 align:middle line:84%
of our ancestors will be
fulfilled, of a new world where

00:42:37.430 --> 00:42:39.890 align:middle line:90%
people work together.

00:42:39.890 --> 00:42:42.300 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not saying that
we lose our culture

00:42:42.300 --> 00:42:43.310 align:middle line:90%
or our individuality.

00:42:43.310 --> 00:42:46.100 align:middle line:84%
I think we're always
going to have our culture,

00:42:46.100 --> 00:42:47.630 align:middle line:90%
our music, our food.

00:42:47.630 --> 00:42:50.965 align:middle line:84%
But I think on a global
level, people-- people ask me,

00:42:50.965 --> 00:42:52.340 align:middle line:84%
they asked me at
this conference,

00:42:52.340 --> 00:42:54.770 align:middle line:84%
are we moving toward
a global government?

00:42:54.770 --> 00:42:58.190 align:middle line:84%
And I say, how would you
know when it happens?

00:42:58.190 --> 00:42:59.750 align:middle line:90%
How would you define that?

00:42:59.750 --> 00:43:01.940 align:middle line:90%
We already have global commerce.

00:43:01.940 --> 00:43:04.400 align:middle line:84%
We're moving toward a
global financial system.

00:43:04.400 --> 00:43:07.550 align:middle line:90%
We've got 24/7 trading.

00:43:07.550 --> 00:43:09.330 align:middle line:90%
We've got global security.

00:43:09.330 --> 00:43:12.020 align:middle line:84%
We've got global trade
of global resources.

00:43:12.020 --> 00:43:14.690 align:middle line:84%
We're sharing global
medicines, deployment of troops

00:43:14.690 --> 00:43:18.050 align:middle line:90%
to help with global crises.

00:43:18.050 --> 00:43:19.550 align:middle line:84%
What would have
to happen for you

00:43:19.550 --> 00:43:24.230 align:middle line:84%
to say that we have or we
don't have a global government?

00:43:24.230 --> 00:43:26.490 align:middle line:84%
And so then the next
question is people say, well,

00:43:26.490 --> 00:43:28.030 align:middle line:90%
is it a good thing?

00:43:28.030 --> 00:43:29.030 align:middle line:90%
And I can't answer that.

00:43:29.030 --> 00:43:30.863 align:middle line:84%
I say, I don't know the
answer, because it's

00:43:30.863 --> 00:43:33.050 align:middle line:84%
all about how it
would be implemented.

00:43:33.050 --> 00:43:38.420 align:middle line:84%
If we'll learn, as a
planet, to share the things

00:43:38.420 --> 00:43:41.930 align:middle line:84%
that every human needs every day
of their lives to be healthy,

00:43:41.930 --> 00:43:44.630 align:middle line:90%
vital, thriving humans--

00:43:44.630 --> 00:43:48.960 align:middle line:84%
fresh water, clean food,
medicines, and the opportunity

00:43:48.960 --> 00:43:50.440 align:middle line:90%
to create a better life.

00:43:50.440 --> 00:43:52.640 align:middle line:84%
And that is shared
equally, but we still

00:43:52.640 --> 00:43:55.400 align:middle line:84%
retain our culture and our food
and our art and rock and roll

00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:57.500 align:middle line:84%
music and all that stuff,
it can be very cool.

00:43:57.500 --> 00:44:01.160 align:middle line:84%
If globalization is pushed
to a deeper level out

00:44:01.160 --> 00:44:06.260 align:middle line:84%
of greed and competition, it
could be a really ugly way

00:44:06.260 --> 00:44:07.120 align:middle line:90%
to go.

00:44:07.120 --> 00:44:09.680 align:middle line:84%
>> And Gregg, is there a
possibility that we're looking

00:44:09.680 --> 00:44:13.817 align:middle line:84%
